dataLineage.statement:
This layer was downloaded by ITOS as a shapefile from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Created and populated reference name field. 2. Admin3 units "Gomon" and "Sikensi" incorrectly had "CI3102" as their Admin2 p-codes. "CI3102" is the p-code for Admin2 unit "Kong". They were given the p-code "CI0302" for Admin2 "Sikensi", which is what they have Admin2 name attribution for and where they are spatially located.
By doing this, it also fixed 2 duplicate p-code errors: -Admin3 units "Oumé" and "Sikensi" both used p-code "CI130201" -Admin3 units "Diégonéfla" and "Gomon" both used p-code "CI130202"
3. Fixed 1 gap error and 1 overlap error. 4. Fixed 3 small Nesting Errors with Admin1 and 2 in Admin3 "Parc National de Bona".
